 Independent pronouns are used with the stabilizer (cee/nee) in
 nonverbal sentences and as the focus in verbal sentences.  It is also
 used for direct object when the it doesn't follow the verb (when an
 indirect object separates it from the verb).  It appears in a subject
 position when conjoined with another NP ('we and they', 'I and the
 girl') or modified by some determiner or relative clause ('the her I
 was talking about').

