 The conjuntion 'dà' ('and'), is used to join NPs or post-nominal
 adjectives, but not sentences.  It may optionally appear in front of
 the first item, as well as between all the joined items.  Joining
 sentences is done by placing them next to one another.  In this way,
 'we ate and drank', becomes 'mun ci mun sha' or 'we ate we drank'.  Is
 this a phenomenon that can be covered in the grammar matrix?  I'm
